                <li>5 <span class="cross"></span> Temple</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<hr />

<h3 style="margin-bottom:0">Turn Order</h3>
<ol style="margin-top:0">
    <li>Place 1 worker tile
        <ul>
            <li>any rotation</li>
            <li>next to at least 1 jungle tile</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Fill jungle spaces
        <ul>
            <li>2 worker tiles adjacent to empty jungle space <span class="arrow"></span> add jungle tile from display</li>
            <li>Decide order if 2 jungle tiles are needed</li>
            <li>Need 3+ jungle tiles <span class="arrow"></span> place first two tiles, draw 3rd from draw pile</li>
            <li>Skip if the condition is not met or if the jungle tiles are exhausted</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Carry out jungle actions
        <ul>
            <li>Workers on new tile are activated</li>
            <li>Workers adjacent to any new jungle tiles are activated</li>
            <li>May skip or do fewer actions</li>
            <li>May activate in any order, but each set of workers must be completed before moving to next</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Refill
        <ul>
            <li>Draw back up to 3 worker tiles</li>
            <li>Refill jungle display</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ol>

<hr />

<div class="table">
    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <h4 style="margin-bottom:0">Map</h4>
            <ul style="margin-top:0">
                <li>2 maps per player</li>
                <li>Draw pile <span class="arrow"></span> map board <span class="arrow"></span> display</li>
                <li>Spend map tokens to take tiles from map board</li>
                <li>Refresh map and display at end of turn</li>
                <li>Leftover maps are worth 0 gold</li>
                <li>Variant: allow overbuilding when <i>draw pile</i> is depleted</li>
            </ul>

            <h4 style="margin-bottom:0">Irrigation</h4>
            <ul style="margin-top:0">
                <li>Water carrier backward 1 space per worker</li>
                <li>Take 4 cacao per worker</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h4 style="margin-bottom:0">Chocolate</h4>
            <ul style="margin-top:0">
                <li>Kitchen: each worker replaces a cacao with a chocolate</li>
                <li>Leftover chocolate is worth 0 gold</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h4 style="margin-bottom:0">Hut</h4>
            <ul style="margin-top:0">
                <li>Randomize the 12 hut tiles, arrange low to high</li>
                <li>Turn end: may buy 1 hut</li>
                <li><i>May</i> build duplicate huts</li>
                <li>Huts are worth buy price</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <h4></h4>
            <h4 style="margin-bottom:0">The Gem Mines</h4>
            <ul style="margin-top:0">
                <li>Add 6 gems when a Gem Mine is <i>revealed</i></li>
                <li>1 gem of each color <span class="arrow"></span> exchange for <i>lowest</i> mask (mandatory)</li>
                <li>Resolve gem distribution in clockwise order</li>
                <li>Add mask values to gold, each leftover gem is worth 1 gold</li>
            </ul>

            <h4 style="margin-bottom:0">Favor of the Emperor</h4>
            <ul style="margin-top:0">
                <li>Place emperor on $2 market (or water tile)</li>
                <li>Move emperor to your worker tile when placed in same row/column</li>
                <li>Take $1 when emperor is moved to your worker tile</li>
                <li>Take $1 if emperor is on your tile at start of turn</li>
            </ul>

            <h4 style="margin-bottom:0">The New Workers</h4>
            <ul style="margin-top:0">
                <li>Either add to original tiles, or replace some</li>
                <li>All players should use the same number and combination</li>
                <li>Total worker tiles should outnumber jungle tiles
                    <ul>
                        <li>2p: 1-8 more worker</li>
                        <li>3p: 2-12 more worker</li>
                        <li>4p: 3-16 more worker</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

